      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2017-11-07 23:56:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nWe don't need to do OST migration for a released file if an admin is removing an OST, since the released file does not actually use any OST.  It would be desirable (in a separate patch) to be able to update the layout on a released file according to the migrate request.  Is there a ticket open for that yet?\n\nSeparately, the other question is what to do with MDT inode migration?  If an admin wants to evacuate an MDT in DNE (or e.g. migrate user subdirectories off MDT0000) I believe that the current code will block the migration because the FID will change, but we should figure out some way to handle this.  If we could update/deprecate the lhsm-posix tool and move to archive identifiers store in Lustre xattrs instead of Lustre FIDs stored in the archive, we could allow the migration to proceed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
